ides feedback on invalid syntax.",[25,228,63],{"id":62},[38,230,231],{},[41,232,233,236],{},[44,234,235],{},"Rust",": A systems programming language that runs blazingly fast, prevents segfaults, and guarantees thread safety.",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":238},[239,240,241],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":62,"depth":98,"text":63},"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/16349CIC6DYXDHTwt75gVh1bworLk95VZ","A pseudo code interpreter written in rust that interprets pseudocode file passed to it as cli argument.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/pseudo_interpreter",[],{},{"icon":116},"/projects/pseudo-code-interpreter",{"title":197,"description":243},[235],"projects/pseudo-code-interpreter","jnEnpYfGZidqoU8m6zY5k-kKZI5XPlDZpo9bpEmSW9U",{"id":254,"title":255,"body":256,"coverImage":242,"description":335,"extension":105,"github":336,"images":337,"liveUrl":339,"meta":340,"navigation":341,"path":342,"rank":98,"seo":343,"slug":120,"stack":344,"stem":345,"__hash__":346},"projects/projects/pseudo-runner.md","Pseudo Runner",{"type":22,"value":257,"toc":329},[258,260,263,265,291,295,303,307],[25,259,28],{"id":27},[30,261,262],{},"Pseudo Runner is a VS Code extension that allows you to write and execute pseudo code directly within the editor. It provides syntax highlighting, code execution, and output display all in one place.",[25,264,36],{"id":35},[38,266,267,273,279,285],{},[41,268,269,272],{},[44,270,271],{},"Syntax Highlighting",": Full pseudo code syntax support",[41,274,275,278],{},[44,276,277],{},"In-Editor Execution",": Run your pseudo code without leaving VS Code",[41,280,281,284],{},[44,282,283],{},"Output Panel",": See execution results in a dedicated output panel",[41,286,287,290],{},[44,288,289],{},"Error Reporting",": Clear error messages with line numbers",[25,292,294],{"id":293},"how-it-works","How It Works",[30,296,297,298,302],{},"The extension registers a custom language mode for ",[299,300,301],"code",{},".pseudo"," files and provides a built-in interpreter that parses and executes the code. Results are displayed in the VS Code output panel.",[25,304,306],{"id":305},"getting-started","Getting Started",[308,309,310,313,319,322],"ol",{},[41,311,312],{},"Install the extension from the VS Code Marketplace",[41,314,315,316,318],{},"Create a new file with the ",[299,317,301],{}," extension",[41,320,321],{},"Write your pseudo code",[41,323,324,325,328],{},"Press ",[299,326,327],{},"Ctrl+Shift+P"," and run \"Pseudo Runner: Execute\"",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":330},[331,332,333,334],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":293,"depth":98,"text":294},{"id":305,"depth":98,"text":306},"A VS Code extension that runs pseudo code files directly in the editor.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/pseudo-runner",[242,338],"https://image2url.com/r2/default/images/1772468076141-94683d8e-029b-4887-843f-99970e779057.png","https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/publishers/Kratosgado",{},{"icon":116},"/projects/pseudo-runner",{"title":255,"description":335},[82,164],"projects/pseudo-runner","W5rtk6_An8UrQxub8WWh-MesKC1FS88fqXDuzXOYaSg",{"id":348,"title":349,"body":350,"coverImage":394,"description":395,"extension":105,"github":396,"images":397,"liveUrl":396,"meta":399,"navigation":400,"path":401,"rank":402,"seo":403,"slug":120,"stack":404,"stem":406,"__hash__":407},"projects/projects/autoscroll-web-extension.md","AutoScroll Web Extension",{"type":22,"value":351,"toc":389},[352,354,357,359,373,375],[25,353,28],{"id":27},[30,355,356],{},"AutoScroll Web Extension is a project that automatically scrolls the page for you.",[25,358,36],{"id":35},[38,360,361,367],{},[41,362,363,366],{},[44,364,365],{},"Automated Scrolling",": Hand-free scrolling experience.",[41,368,369,372],{},[44,370,371],{},"Configurable",": Settings to adjust scroll speed and behavior.",[25,374,63],{"id":62},[38,376,377,383],{},[41,378,379,382],{},[44,380,381],{},"JavaScript",": Core logic i